Strongylognathus karawajewi
Pisarski, 1966: 521, w, Ukraine; 
Radchenko 1985
: 1519, q; 
Radchenko 1991
: 88, m; all subsequent authors.

Strongylognathus karawajewi

was described, based on workers from the southern coast of Crimea (vill. Magarach, now Otradnoye near Yalta, material from the collection of W. A. Karawajew, ZISK) by 
Pisarski (1966)
. Later, it was recorded from the western Caucasus (
Arnoldi and Dlussky 1978
), the Kopetdagh Mts. (
Dlussky and Zabelin 1985
, 
Dlussky et al. 1990
), Armenia and Hissar Range in Tadzhikistan (
Radchenko 1991
) and Turkey (
Kiran et al. 2014
); records of this species from China were based on misidentifications (
Radchenko et al. 2017
). Queens of 

S. karawajewi

were described by 
Radchenko (1985)
from Crimea and males - from Crimea, Armenia and Tajikistan (
Radchenko 1991
).
